{
  "stem": "1895.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so after this deportation, they took the people that they left over in this two block area, and under the direction of the Germans, they went house by house, block by block, street by street, and they stripped everything that was left over, and took everything that was worthwhile, packed it, and shipped it to Germany.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was the main reason why they left the 3,000 people, to do cleanup work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were also kept for another reason.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some of the people that were left among the 3,000 were tradesmen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were-- they were tailors, they were shoemakers, they were furriers, they were knitters, they were people who knew how to put things together.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And these, the SS hierarchy that was in charge of the Final Solution, left those people, if for no other reason is so that they would continue doing stuff for them, making things for them, which they eventually shipped home and enriched themselves with.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because looking back at it from-- with hindsight, I can see now that the toyed with Jews like a cat toys with a mouse.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They figured these Jews are condemned anyway.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They're going to die sooner or later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Why can't they make some leather coats for us, or why can't they make some uniforms for us, or why can't they-- why can't they make some furniture for us, and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this is what they used them for.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the 3,000 people that were left in the ghetto were being eliminated slowly.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they had different, what we called actions.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, like they would come in-- I know that two of my uncles that survived, two of my uncles-- one was my father's brother, Hershel.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
